People keep saying about genetic defects as a consequence of incest. This is true but such traits only appear after multiple generations of inbreeding. Isolated cases of incest in a massively diverse gene pool don't make a damp in the first generation.

Depending on the population size and diversity of the gene pool, a normal couple is also at the risk of having babies with genetic disorders if they were happened to carry dormant genes of the disorder.
